    <statement><p>Simplify the function formula, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ H(r) = {\frac{r^{3}-49r}{r^{3}+8r^{2}+7r}} }</m></p>
<p>Reduced <m>H(r)=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{r-7}{r+1}, r\ne -7\hbox{ and }r\ne 0</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cancel common factors.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   H(r) \amp = {\frac{r^{3}-49r}{r^{3}+8r^{2}+7r}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{r\mathopen{}\left(r^{2}-49\right)}}{{r\mathopen{}\left(r^{2}+8r+7\right)}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{r\mathopen{}\left(r+7\right)\mathopen{}\left(r-7\right)}}{{r\mathopen{}\left(r+7\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+1\right)}} \\
                 \amp = {\frac{r-7}{r+1}, r\ne -7\hbox{ and }r\ne 0}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since <m>r(r+7)</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the reduction is <m>r \ne {-7, 0}</m>.</p>
</solution>
